BRISTOL-MYERS Co. (New York) -- Stephen Keith Carter was named president of the pharmaceutical research and development division of this health-care products firm.
He had been senior vice president of pharmaceutical and medical development in the division.
Jerome Birnbaum was named to the newly created post of executive vice president of research in the division.
Mr. Carter succeeds Giulio Vita, who remains a vice president of the corporation and takes the newly created post of senior vice president and scientific adviser to the Science & Technology Group. 

